游戏发行前，获2012年{{le|IndieCade|IndieCade}}视觉设计奖<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2012/10/11/indiecade-2012-winners-get-their-crowns-indiecade-east-in-2013/ |title=IndieCade 2012 winners get their crowns, IndieCade East in 2013 |date=2013-10-11 |accessdate=2018-01-12 |first=Jessica |last=Conditt |work=Engadget (Joystiq) |archive-date=2019-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213095139/https://www.engadget.com/2012/10/11/indiecade-2012-winners-get-their-crowns-indiecade-east-in-2013/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>、2013年Good Game Club最高奖<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.engadget.com/2013/11/19/good-game-club-picks-hand-drawn-puzzler-gorogoa-for-top-prize/ |title=Good Game Club picks hand-drawn puzzler Gorogoa for top prize |date=2013-11-19 |accessdate=2018-01-12 |first=Jessica |last=Conditt |work=Engadget (Joystiq) |archive-date=2018-10-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181018201603/https://www.engadget.com/2013/11/19/good-game-club-picks-hand-drawn-puzzler-gorogoa-for-top-prize/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>、2014年[[独立游戏节|独立游戏节]]优秀视觉艺术奖及设计和剧情类荣誉奖<ref name="igf"/>。

游戏完整发布后获评论人普遍好评，其中PC版在[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]获84/100分<ref name="MCPC" />，iOS版获91/100分<ref name="MCiOS" />。评论人尤其看好游戏的插画和图像。《[[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]]》的山姆·马赫科维奇（Sam Machkovech）指游戏是“有史以来最出色的手绘电子游戏”<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2017/12/gorogoa-review-video-games-now-have-their-first-classic-childrens-book/|title=Gorogoa review: Beneath four panels hide gaming’s most beautiful surprise|last=Machkovech|first=Sam|date=2017-12-12|work=Ars Technica|accessdate=2017-12-14|archive-date=2021-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210118001905/https://arstechnica.com/gaming/2017/12/gorogoa-review-video-games-now-have-their-first-classic-childrens-book/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，《[[PC_Gamer|PC Gamer]]》的菲利帕·沃（Philippa Warr）认为游戏“出奇地惊艳”<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=http://www.pcgamer.com/goragoa-review/|title=Gorogoa Review|last=Warr|first=Philippa|date=2017-12-14|work=PC Gamer|accessdate=2017-12-14|archive-date=2020-12-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201201025149/https://www.pcgamer.com/goragoa-review/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

[[The_Verge|The Verge]]的安德鲁·韦伯斯特（Andrew Webster）称赞游戏没有尿点，很少有卡关或无法解决谜题的情况，认为这应该归功于游戏设计；瓦尔对此表示认同<ref name=":2" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/12/14/16774194/gorogoa-game-review-iphone-switch-steam|title=This soothing, intricate puzzle game will make you feel like a genius|last=Webster|first=Andrew|date=2017-12-14|work=The Verge|accessdate=2017-12-14|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109021927/https://www.theverge.com/2017/12/14/16774194/gorogoa-game-review-iphone-switch-steam|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[VentureBeat|VentureBeat]]的史蒂芬妮·陈（Stephanie Chan）赞扬游戏易于操作，解谜后有成就感<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/12/13/gorogoa-review-a-brief-but-beautiful-foray-into-an-otherworldly-mystery/|title=Gorogoa review — a brief but beautiful foray into an otherworldly mystery|last=Chan|first=Stephanie|date=2017-12-13|work=VentureBeat|accessdate=2017-12-14|archive-date=2021-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210129181306/https://venturebeat.com/2017/12/13/gorogoa-review-a-brief-but-beautiful-foray-into-an-otherworldly-mystery/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。Jump Dash Roll的罗伯·克肖（Rob Kershaw）表示认同，称游戏的插画“非常美观”，是“游戏设计的奇观”<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kershaw|first1=Rob|title=Jump Dash Roll {{!}} Gorogoa Review|url=https://www.jumpdashroll.com/article/gorogoa|website=Jump Dash Roll|accessdate=2018-03-19|archive-date=2020-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922074058/https://www.jumpdashroll.com/article/gorogoa|dead-url=no}}</ref>。但另一方面，马赫科维奇认为部分关卡解谜路线不清晰，令人恼火<ref name=":1" />。他认为，游戏两到三个小时的通关流程是“麻雀虽小，但五脏俱全”，但也希望流程能长一点<ref name=":1" />。沃等评论人表示希望打通多个周目，以此消化剧情<ref name=":2" />。

